{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1126,"text":"Over the past 10 years,"},{"time":2445,"text":"I've been researching the way\npeople organize and visualize information."},{"time":7786,"text":"And I've noticed an interesting shift."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10166,"text":"For a long period of time,"},{"time":11910,"text":"we believed in a natural ranking order\nin the world around us,"},{"time":16362,"text":"also known as the great chain of being,\nor \"Scala naturae\" in Latin,"},{"time":21131,"text":"a top-down structure that normally starts\nwith God at the very top,"},{"time":25330,"text":"followed by angels, noblemen,"},{"time":27759,"text":"common people, animals, and so on."},{"time":31999,"text":"This idea was actually based\non Aristotle's ontology,"},{"time":36298,"text":"which classified all things known to man\nin a set of opposing categories,"},{"time":40766,"text":"like the ones you see behind me."},{"time":44687,"text":"But over time, interestingly enough,"},{"time":47458,"text":"this concept adopted\nthe branching schema of a tree"},{"time":51628,"text":"in what became known\nas the Porphyrian tree,"},{"time":54525,"text":"also considered to be\nthe oldest tree of knowledge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59238,"text":"The branching scheme\nof the tree was, in fact,"},{"time":61436,"text":"such a powerful metaphor\nfor conveying information"},{"time":64409,"text":"that it became, over time,\nan important communication tool"},{"time":67703,"text":"to map a variety of systems of knowledge."},{"time":70648,"text":"We can see trees being used\nto map morality,"},{"time":73755,"text":"with the popular tree of virtues\nand tree of vices,"},{"time":76628,"text":"as you can see here, with these beautiful\nillustrations from medieval Europe."},{"time":80825,"text":"We can see trees being used\nto map consanguinity,"},{"time":83937,"text":"the various blood ties between people."},{"time":87110,"text":"We can also see trees being used\nto map genealogy,"},{"time":90230,"text":"perhaps the most famous archetype\nof the tree diagram."},{"time":93064,"text":"I think many of you in the audience\nhave probably seen family trees."},{"time":96404,"text":"Many of you probably even have\nyour own family trees drawn in such a way."},{"time":101158,"text":"We can see trees even mapping\nsystems of law,"},{"time":104093,"text":"the various decrees and rulings\nof kings and rulers."},{"time":109785,"text":"And finally, of course,\nalso a very popular scientific metaphor,"},{"time":113567,"text":"we can see trees being used\nto map all species known to man."},{"time":119177,"text":"And trees ultimately became\nsuch a powerful visual metaphor"},{"time":123107,"text":"because in many ways,\nthey really embody this human desire"},{"time":125999,"text":"for order, for balance,\nfor unity, for symmetry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129999,"text":"However, nowadays we are really facing\nnew complex, intricate challenges"},{"time":134346,"text":"that cannot be understood by simply\nemploying a simple tree diagram."},{"time":140037,"text":"And a new metaphor is currently emerging,"},{"time":143303,"text":"and it's currently replacing the tree"},{"time":145477,"text":"in visualizing various\nsystems of knowledge."},{"time":148064,"text":"It's really providing us with a new lens\nto understand the world around us."},{"time":153495,"text":"And this new metaphor\nis the metaphor of the network."},{"time":157511,"text":"And we can see this shift\nfrom trees into networks"},{"time":160846,"text":"in many domains of knowledge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162510,"text":"We can see this shift in the way\nwe try to understand the brain."},{"time":168453,"text":"While before, we used\nto think of the brain"},{"time":170515,"text":"as a modular, centralized organ,"},{"time":172530,"text":"where a given area was responsible\nfor a set of actions and behaviors,"},{"time":176592,"text":"the more we know about the brain,"},{"time":178355,"text":"the more we think of it\nas a large music symphony,"},{"time":181665,"text":"played by hundreds\nand thousands of instruments."},{"time":184299,"text":"This is a beautiful snapshot\ncreated by the Blue Brain Project,"},{"time":187999,"text":"where you can see 10,000 neurons\nand 30 million connections."},{"time":192736,"text":"And this is only mapping 10 percent\nof a mammalian neocortex."},{"time":198815,"text":"We can also see this shift in the way\nwe try to conceive of human knowledge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204062,"text":"These are some remarkable trees\nof knowledge, or trees of science,"},{"time":207234,"text":"by Spanish scholar Ramon Llull."},{"time":209999,"text":"And Llull was actually the precursor,"},{"time":211833,"text":"the very first one who created\nthe metaphor of science as a tree,"},{"time":215571,"text":"a metaphor we use\nevery single day, when we say,"},{"time":218563,"text":"\"Biology is a branch of science,\""},{"time":220252,"text":"when we say,"},{"time":221429,"text":"\"Genetics is a branch of science.\""},{"time":224283,"text":"But perhaps the most beautiful of all\ntrees of knowledge, at least for me,"},{"time":227902,"text":"was created for the French encyclopedia\nby Diderot and d'Alembert in 1751."},{"time":232378,"text":"This was really the bastion\nof the French Enlightenment,"},{"time":235037,"text":"and this gorgeous illustration\nwas featured as a table of contents"},{"time":238886,"text":"for the encyclopedia."},{"time":240481,"text":"And it actually maps out\nall domains of knowledge"},{"time":244692,"text":"as separate branches of a tree."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247866,"text":"But knowledge is much more\nintricate than this."},{"time":250794,"text":"These are two maps of Wikipedia\nshowing the inter-linkage of articles --"},{"time":255458,"text":"related to history on the left,\nand mathematics on the right."},{"time":259966,"text":"And I think by looking at these maps"},{"time":261729,"text":"and other ones that have been\ncreated of Wikipedia --"},{"time":264297,"text":"arguably one of the largest rhizomatic\nstructures ever created by man --"},{"time":267713,"text":"we can really understand\nhow human knowledge is much more intricate"},{"time":271559,"text":"and interdependent, just like a network."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275455,"text":"We can also see this interesting shift"},{"time":277642,"text":"in the way we map\nsocial ties between people."},{"time":281524,"text":"This is the typical organization chart."},{"time":283843,"text":"I'm assuming many of you have seen\na similar chart as well,"},{"time":286661,"text":"in your own corporations, or others."},{"time":288431,"text":"It's a top-down structure"},{"time":289940,"text":"that normally starts\nwith the CEO at the very top,"},{"time":292825,"text":"and where you can drill down all the way\nto the individual workmen on the bottom."},{"time":297634,"text":"But humans sometimes are, well, actually,\nall humans are unique in their own way,"},{"time":302506,"text":"and sometimes you really don't play well\nunder this really rigid structure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308711,"text":"I think the Internet is really changing\nthis paradigm quite a lot."},{"time":311845,"text":"This is a fantastic map\nof online social collaboration"},{"time":315234,"text":"between Perl developers."},{"time":316887,"text":"Perl is a famous programming language,"},{"time":318999,"text":"and here, you can see\nhow different programmers"},{"time":321746,"text":"are actually exchanging files,\nand working together on a given project."},{"time":325597,"text":"And here, you can notice that this is\na completely decentralized process --"},{"time":329799,"text":"there's no leader in this organization,"},{"time":331979,"text":"it's a network."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334337,"text":"We can also see this interesting shift\nwhen we look at terrorism."},{"time":339613,"text":"One of the main challenges\nof understanding terrorism nowadays"},{"time":342741,"text":"is that we are dealing with\ndecentralized, independent cells,"},{"time":346495,"text":"where there's no leader\nleading the whole process."},{"time":350518,"text":"And here, you can actually see\nhow visualization is being used."},{"time":353840,"text":"The diagram that you see behind me"},{"time":355521,"text":"shows all the terrorists involved\nin the Madrid attack in 2004."},{"time":359942,"text":"And what they did here is,\nthey actually segmented the network"},{"time":362893,"text":"into three different years,"},{"time":364416,"text":"represented by the vertical layers\nthat you see behind me."},{"time":367482,"text":"And the blue lines tie together"},{"time":369475,"text":"the people that were present\nin that network year after year."},{"time":373117,"text":"So even though there's no leader per se,"},{"time":375169,"text":"these people are probably the most\ninfluential ones in that organization,"},{"time":378828,"text":"the ones that know more about the past,"},{"time":380860,"text":"and the future plans and goals\nof this particular cell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385232,"text":"We can also see this shift\nfrom trees into networks"},{"time":388262,"text":"in the way we classify\nand organize species."},{"time":393245,"text":"The image on the right\nis the only illustration"},{"time":396098,"text":"that Darwin included\nin \"The Origin of Species,\""},{"time":399234,"text":"which Darwin called the \"Tree of Life.\""},{"time":402098,"text":"There's actually a letter\nfrom Darwin to the publisher,"},{"time":405007,"text":"expanding on the importance\nof this particular diagram."},{"time":407687,"text":"It was critical for Darwin's\ntheory of evolution."},{"time":411408,"text":"But recently, scientists discovered\nthat overlaying this tree of life"},{"time":414999,"text":"is a dense network of bacteria,"},{"time":417458,"text":"and these bacteria\nare actually tying together"},{"time":419643,"text":"species that were completely\nseparated before,"},{"time":421839,"text":"to what scientists are now calling\nnot the tree of life,"},{"time":424943,"text":"but the web of life, the network of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429489,"text":"And finally, we can really\nsee this shift, again,"},{"time":432027,"text":"when we look at ecosystems\naround our planet."},{"time":435599,"text":"No more do we have these simplified\npredator-versus-prey diagrams"},{"time":438789,"text":"we have all learned at school."},{"time":441201,"text":"This is a much more accurate\ndepiction of an ecosystem."},{"time":444214,"text":"This is a diagram created\nby Professor David Lavigne,"},{"time":447142,"text":"mapping close to 100 species\nthat interact with the codfish"},{"time":450666,"text":"off the coast of Newfoundland in Canada."},{"time":454244,"text":"And I think here, we can really understand\nthe intricate and interdependent nature"},{"time":458205,"text":"of most ecosystems\nthat abound on our planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462442,"text":"But even though recent,\nthis metaphor of the network,"},{"time":466110,"text":"is really already adopting\nvarious shapes and forms,"},{"time":469237,"text":"and it's almost becoming\na growing visual taxonomy."},{"time":471724,"text":"It's almost becoming\nthe syntax of a new language."},{"time":474395,"text":"And this is one aspect\nthat truly fascinates me."},{"time":477678,"text":"And these are actually\n15 different typologies"},{"time":480235,"text":"I've been collecting over time,"},{"time":482394,"text":"and it really shows the immense\nvisual diversity of this new metaphor."},{"time":487001,"text":"And here is an example."},{"time":488818,"text":"On the very top band,\nyou have radial convergence,"},{"time":492775,"text":"a visualization model that has become\nreally popular over the last five years."},{"time":497198,"text":"At the top left, the very first project\nis a gene network,"},{"time":501576,"text":"followed by a network\nof IP addresses -- machines, servers --"},{"time":505609,"text":"followed by a network of Facebook friends."},{"time":509240,"text":"You probably couldn't find\nmore disparate topics,"},{"time":511772,"text":"yet they are using the same metaphor,\nthe same visual model,"},{"time":515590,"text":"to map the never-ending complexities\nof its own subject."},{"time":520545,"text":"And here are a few more examples\nof the many I've been collecting,"},{"time":523693,"text":"of this growing visual\ntaxonomy of networks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528248,"text":"But networks are not just\na scientific metaphor."},{"time":532192,"text":"As designers, researchers, and scientists\ntry to map a variety of complex systems,"},{"time":537757,"text":"they are in many ways influencing\ntraditional art fields,"},{"time":540594,"text":"like painting and sculpture,"},{"time":542020,"text":"and influencing many different artists."},{"time":544718,"text":"And perhaps because networks have\nthis huge aesthetical force to them --"},{"time":548784,"text":"they're immensely gorgeous --"},{"time":550766,"text":"they are really becoming a cultural meme,"},{"time":552846,"text":"and driving a new art movement,\nwhich I've called \"networkism.\""},{"time":558544,"text":"And we can see this influence\nin this movement in a variety of ways."},{"time":561776,"text":"This is just one of many examples,"},{"time":563593,"text":"where you can see this influence\nfrom science into art."},{"time":566342,"text":"The example on your left side\nis IP-mapping,"},{"time":569237,"text":"a computer-generated map of IP addresses;\nagain -- servers, machines."},{"time":573253,"text":"And on your right side,"},{"time":574482,"text":"you have \"Transient Structures\nand Unstable Networks\" by Sharon Molloy,"},{"time":579124,"text":"using oil and enamel on canvas."},{"time":581870,"text":"And here are a few more\npaintings by Sharon Molloy,"},{"time":584999,"text":"some gorgeous, intricate paintings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588375,"text":"And here's another example\nof that interesting cross-pollination"},{"time":591705,"text":"between science and art."},{"time":593475,"text":"On your left side,\nyou have \"Operation Smile.\""},{"time":596164,"text":"It is a computer-generated map\nof a social network."},{"time":599077,"text":"And on your right side,\nyou have \"Field 4,\" by Emma McNally,"},{"time":602827,"text":"using only graphite on paper."},{"time":605374,"text":"Emma McNally is one of the main\nleaders of this movement,"},{"time":608915,"text":"and she creates these striking,\nimaginary landscapes,"},{"time":611508,"text":"where you can really notice the influence\nfrom traditional network visualization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618324,"text":"But networkism doesn't happen\nonly in two dimensions."},{"time":621355,"text":"This is perhaps\none of my favorite projects"},{"time":623657,"text":"of this new movement."},{"time":625086,"text":"And I think the title really\nsays it all -- it's called:"},{"time":627744,"text":"\"Galaxies Forming Along Filaments,"},{"time":629935,"text":"Like Droplets Along the Strands\nof a Spider's Web.\""},{"time":634616,"text":"And I just find this particular project\nto be immensely powerful."},{"time":637720,"text":"It was created by Tomás Saraceno,"},{"time":639704,"text":"and he occupies these large spaces,"},{"time":642426,"text":"creates these massive installations\nusing only elastic ropes."},{"time":645792,"text":"As you actually navigate that space\nand bounce along those elastic ropes,"},{"time":649633,"text":"the entire network kind of shifts,\nalmost like a real organic network would."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655414,"text":"And here's yet another example"},{"time":657470,"text":"of networkism taken\nto a whole different level."},{"time":660303,"text":"This was created\nby Japanese artist Chiharu Shiota"},{"time":663540,"text":"in a piece called \"In Silence.\""},{"time":665834,"text":"And Chiharu, like Tomás Saraceno,\nfills these rooms with this dense network,"},{"time":671213,"text":"this dense web of elastic ropes\nand black wool and thread,"},{"time":674999,"text":"sometimes including objects,\nas you can see here,"},{"time":677782,"text":"sometimes even including people,\nin many of her installations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683374,"text":"But networks are also\nnot just a new trend,"},{"time":686089,"text":"and it's too easy for us\nto dismiss it as such."},{"time":689029,"text":"Networks really embody\nnotions of decentralization,"},{"time":692660,"text":"of interconnectedness, of interdependence."},{"time":696303,"text":"And this new way of thinking is critical"},{"time":698803,"text":"for us to solve many of the complex\nproblems we are facing nowadays,"},{"time":702557,"text":"from decoding the human brain,"},{"time":704422,"text":"to understanding\nthe vast universe out there."},{"time":707746,"text":"On your left side, you have a snapshot\nof a neural network of a mouse --"},{"time":712259,"text":"very similar to our own\nat this particular scale."},{"time":715500,"text":"And on your right side, you have\nthe Millennium Simulation."},{"time":718490,"text":"It was the largest\nand most realistic simulation"},{"time":721262,"text":"of the growth of cosmic structure."},{"time":723490,"text":"It was able to recreate the history\nof 20 million galaxies"},{"time":728030,"text":"in approximately 25 terabytes of output."},{"time":732081,"text":"And coincidentally or not,"},{"time":733518,"text":"I just find this particular comparison"},{"time":735415,"text":"between the smallest scale\nof knowledge -- the brain --"},{"time":738142,"text":"and the largest scale of knowledge --\nthe universe itself --"},{"time":740995,"text":"to be really quite striking\nand fascinating."},{"time":743807,"text":"Because as Bruce Mau once said,"},{"time":746465,"text":"\"When everything is connected\nto everything else,"},{"time":748901,"text":"for better or for worse,\neverything matters.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":751322,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752497,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}